60 km** was generated to analyze the spatial distribution of satellite images and land cover patterns across the region.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Methodology\n\nThe workflow of the proposed system consists of the following steps:\n\n1. **Data Collection**\n\n   * Sentinel-2 RGB satellite tiles\n   * ESA WorldCover 2021 land cover raster\n   * Delhi NCR boundary GeoJSON\n\n2. **Spatial Filtering**\n\n   * Extract geographic coordinates from image filenames\n   * Convert coordinates into GeoDataFrame\n   * Filter satellite tiles that fall within the Delhi NCR boundary\n\n3. **Spatial Grid Generation**\n\n   * Convert geographic coordinates to UTM projection\n   * Generate a spatial grid of **60 km × 60 km**\n   * Assign satellite tiles to corresponding grid cells\n\n4. **Land Cover Label Extraction**\n\n   * Use ESA WorldCover raster\n   * Sample raster values at satellite tile locations\n   * Assign land cover labels to each satellite image\n\n5. **Deep Learning Model**\n\n   * Use a pretrained **ResNet-18 convolutional neural network**\n   * Replace the final classification layer with 5 output classes\n   * Train using cross-entropy loss and Adam optimizer\n\n6. **Evaluation**\n\n   * Accuracy score\n   * Weighted F1 score\n   * Confusion matrix visualization\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"!pip install geopandas rasterio shapely matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn tqdm opencv-python torch torchvision\n\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-09T06:41:58.499552Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-09T06:41:58.499925Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-09T06:42:03.472538Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-09T06:41:58.499901Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-09T06:42:03.469278Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Requirement already satisfied: geopandas in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (1.1.2)\nRequirement already satisfied: rasterio in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (1.5.0)\nR